      "message": "Should `asyncResp-\u003eres.jsonValue[jsonKeyName]` always be initialized as an empty array here?\n\nMay it be clearer to keep the old way for the case \u0027io_error\u0027 (https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/88012/4/redfish-core/include/utils/collection.hpp#b51), \nand initialize the array when the members are constructed at https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/88012/4/redfish-core/include/utils/collection.hpp#147?\n\n\n```\nDEL\u003e    nlohmann::json::array_t\u0026 membersArr \u003d\nDEL\u003e      getJsonArrayByPointer(asyncResp-\u003eres.jsonValue, jsonKeyName);\n        \n    if (ec \u003d\u003d boost::system::errc::io_error)\n    {\n        asyncResp-\u003eres.jsonValue[jsonKeyName] \u003d nlohmann::json::array();\n        asyncResp-\u003eres.jsonValue[jsonCountKeyName] \u003d 0;\n        return;\n    }\n```",
      "revId": "8ad7ad964201e63dc935133f63703b3b9ba9f461",
