      "writtenOn": "2026-03-06T16:58:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We need to keep this path non-destructive for aggregated responses. If one source already populated Members and another source later returns io_error, resetting Members to [] would drop the previously merged entries.\n\nMaybe we can handle the io_error case like this instead:\n```\nif (ec \u003d\u003d boost::system::errc::io_error)\n{\n    nlohmann::json\u0026 members \u003d asyncResp-\u003eres.jsonValue[jsonKeyName];\n    asyncResp-\u003eres.jsonValue[jsonCountKeyName] \u003d\n        members.is_array()? members.size() : 0;\n    return;\n}\n```",
